### Audit task decision rows

For tasks that involve examining N items and deciding per item (e.g., "review all tests in a directory and decide keep / delete / rebuild / promote / reclassify per test"), the task entry must include an **audit-decision-row** block. Done means every row has a filled decision — the task is not done if the table exists but rows are blank.

**audit-decision-row block format:**

| Item | Decision | Criterion |
|---|---|---|
| `<item path or name>` | `<keep \| delete \| rebuild \| promote \| reclassify>` | `<one-line reason>` |

**Example — 9-file audit of legacy E2E tests:**

| Item | Decision | Criterion |
|---|---|---|
| `tests/e2e/auth-login.spec.ts` | keep | critical path, canary-eligible, correct layer |
| `tests/e2e/auth-logout.spec.ts` | keep | high tier, self-cleaning |
| `tests/e2e/payment-flow.spec.ts` | rebuild | mutates persistent state — needs cleanup in teardown |
| `tests/e2e/admin-dashboard.spec.ts` | rebuild | depends on seeded fixtures not available in canary |
| `tests/e2e/user-profile.spec.ts` | keep | high tier, read-only |
| `tests/e2e/search.spec.ts` | delete | redundant — covered by smoke layer |
| `tests/e2e/legacy-import.spec.ts` | delete | tests removed feature, never passes |
| `tests/e2e/bulk-actions.spec.ts` | reclassify | wrong layer — should be integration test, not E2E |
| `tests/e2e/notifications.spec.ts` | rebuild | relies on real email sending — needs mailhog substitute |

The audit-decision-row block is part of the task body in the issue (see `issue.md.tmpl`). In this plan document, indicate audit tasks with `[audit: N items]` in the expected outcome column so the task size is visible at a glance.

